{"title_page": "Mauri Valtonen", "text_new": "'''Mauri Valtonen''' is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[astronomer]] and professor at the [[University of Turku]].  His fields of scientific interest include [[active galaxies]], [[cosmology]], and the [[three-body problem]].\n\nValtonen completed a Ph.D. from [[Cambridge University]] in 1975. He served as Director of [[Tuorla Observatory]] from 1980 to 2002 and returned to this position again in 2007.\n\n[[File:BlackHoleDiskFlareInGalaxyOJ287-animation-20200428.webm|thumb|Animation of black hole disk flares in OJ 287]]\nIn 2008, Valtonen led a research team which argued that delay in the periodic outbursts from the nucleus of the active galaxy [[OJ 287]] confirmed [[Albert Einstein]]{{'s }}[[general theory of relativity]].<ref>M. Valtonen et al. (2008), [http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v452/n7189/abs/nature06896.html  A massive binary black-hole system in OJ 287 and a test of general relativity]. ''Nature'', '''452''', 851-853</ref>\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Books by Mauri Valtonen==\n\n*Valtonen, M. &  Karttunen, H. (2006). [http://www.cambridge.org/uk/catalogue/catalogue.asp?isbn=0521852242 The Three-Body Problem]. 251 pages. Cambridge University Press.\n*Byrd, G. G., Chernin A. D. & Valtonen M. (2007). ''[http://urss.ru/cgi-bin/db.pl?lang=en&Languages=2&blang=en&page=Book&id=64082&list=1 Cosmology: Foundations and Frontiers]''. Moscow: URSS.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.astro.utu.fi/OJ287MMVI/ OJ 287 2005-2008 Project] (Tuorla Observatory)\n* [http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=644 A Supermassive Black Hole Pairing] (Centauri Dreams)\n* [http://www.astro.utu.fi/staff/ValtonenMauri.shtml Mauri Valtonen's home page]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valtonen, Mauri}}\n[[Category:21st-century astronomers]]\n[[Category:Finnish astronomers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{Finland-scientist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Mauri Valtonen''' is a [[Finlan